## File
00-meta/beestgraph/3D Knowledge Graph Viewer.md

## Title
3D Knowledge Graph Viewer

## Recommendation Summary

### Intent Assessment
Documents the primary visual interface for beestgraph — a 3D graph viewer with three organizational views (PARA, Zettelkasten, Topic Tree) rendered via Three.js and 3d-force-graph. Serves as both design spec and feature documentation.

### Categorization Changes
- **ZETT**: "none (status: qualifying)" → "content_stage: reference" (System documentation describing a feature. Should be reference stage. Missing content_stage field entirely.)
- **TREE**: "technology/web, meta/pkm" → "meta/beestgraph/architecture, technology/web/frontend" (Primary topic is beestgraph architecture. technology/web/frontend is more specific since this is a Three.js frontend component.)
- **GRAPH**: "Likely has a Document node" → "Ensure Document node exists with edges to Three.js, 3d-force-graph, Next.js, CodeMirror (Tool nodes) and Force-Directed Layout, 3D Graph Visualization (Concept nodes). Verify LINKS_TO edges to PARA Method, Zettelkasten Method, Topic Tree Organization, and MOCs documents." (Key architectural doc that should be well-connected in the graph.)

### Metadata Issues
Missing content_stage field. Tags include 'cytoscape' but body mentions Three.js/3d-force-graph, not Cytoscape — remove the cytoscape tag. Status is qualifying but should be published. Missing created_at and updated_at dates.

